<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>database on Cinderblock</title><link>https://cinderblock.github.io/tags/database/</link><description>Recent content in database on Cinderblock</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://cinderblock.github.io/tags/database/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Prometheus + Grafana monitoring</title><link>https://cinderblock.github.io/p/prometheus--grafana-monitoring/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cinderblock.github.io/p/prometheus--grafana-monitoring/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://cinderblock.github.io/p/prometheus--grafana-monitoring/prometheus-grafana-banner.png" alt="Featured image of post Prometheus + Grafana monitoring" />&lt;h1 id="utilizing-prometheus-db-to-create-grafana-monitoring-dashboards">Utilizing Prometheus DB to create Grafana monitoring dashboards&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>In this guide, I&amp;rsquo;ll be setting up a Prometheus database, and configuring Grafana dashboards for monitoring solutions within my homelab.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>To get started, you&amp;rsquo;ll need:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Systems that need monitored&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Familiarity with Docker and Docker-compose.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>An internal DNS server for name resolution.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>SSL certificates for secure communication&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>Let&amp;rsquo;s get started.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="setup-prometheus">Setup Prometheus&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>On the host you wish to run Prometheus on, go ahead and create a new directory called &lt;code>Prometheus&lt;/code> and create two files in it.&lt;/p>
